    • Method Detail

      • loadShaderProgram

        public static ShaderProgram loadShaderProgram(java.io.File vertFile,
                                              java.io.File fragFile)
        Reads the two specified shader files and compiles the shaders into an OpenGL program format. It is recommended that shaders be stored in the 'assets/shaders' directory (which is not present by default).
        Parameters:
        vertFile - The File to read the vert shader from.
        fragFile - The File to read the frag shader from.
        Returns:
        Returns the ShaderProgram object.

      • bindAttribute

        public void bindAttribute(int attribute,
                          java.lang.String variable)
        Binds an OpenGL attribute to the shader program. This all must be done before the shader program is run.
        Parameters:
        attribute - The OpenGL attribute ID.
        variable - The String form of the attribute variable name.
